[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged over armed shop raid in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 29-year-old man has been charged after two men carried out an armed robbery at a shop in Aberdeen on Sunday morning.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The raid took place at the DSG store on the city's Bankhead Road at about 10:25.
A quantity of cash and cigarettes were stolen.
Police Scotland said inquiries were continuing.
